;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 130%; margin-top: 8px;"&gt; 2024 年 3 月 2 日，特朗普在北卡罗来纳州格林斯伯勒举行的集会上发表讲话。&lt;i&gt;摄影：Bloomberg/Bloomberg&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;据知情人士透露，预计当选总统特朗普&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp1LLmCBIfkpPJlsZlfy9NREO_-0RacGLS_zqvEQqyzpWYmIskvVcILKWjcyoMu9Kpt5j0UgRqJj3-up9foE5Ujm3QwGNfKeqhjaocjOc4zNnuyuKAVyopHQ_R6gT64SC0gx2mcCb2wQVaqheDhvgNe1xFT2lvpmNr9R0K9m-P54uMraZtRVdfK_dmEvlb-x7JuAKdPtBCLCDma28EUHmtQL8_V-DAHcoO0oUqEYPto7h7FuEQA1YJhNXQLSo1nJgGxB64hMkWLB6GwWulmFy3zkN6dCC3TmfXUHhEDh3HO7dPjI-VZvl5n1s3E1HMKrrdEXX4c6tnIWYMEaC8E6MH3Twof7H6JFixdkHMClAZjg_QX4OgKAmJfckZpJ5hzv4OoK74uvOoJX_YEX6WX5PyUZQeOcedYXbmYNKR8kMsjkM-QsVuT4yxrsOHToMner_QvXWjem9G5XNh-gdmnZBLd9lw_crCaw7xxMk3MS9NQOnDBgMne4nWuHSi3-yn-OjBsOXwtow9aQ3sRQOCy8w4KYwEb1rb4x9VGq6R75PrPy9ueMuozxvkvkmDC96jzM13xGUkx0ZiMBYkhtyxOzjcWtPJasITqlRyRvgI_uQWDDu35m0DS7SAkDB2DdATg9qNdyydVn7Hcl3QiKsxWRPcTZXToPgPkldDe2_22uA5QWaF8HsySIsFgcVkptxc0vh_ZNwyngWWmkzbvAv0tzV3FmsFmOJjzJ6C1gTM-eMt8lH0aQwO1ZI1YlnjilhjlSVb4JZl4fR9gFSbSOVrgf0xOsQ%3D%3D" target="_blank"&gt;将在周一援引紧急权力&lt;/a&gt;来释放国内能源生产，同时寻求扭转总统乔·拜登应对气候变化的行动。这些举措以及其他扩大石油和天然气开发的举措将有助于减缓美国在控制温室气体排放方面取得的进展。然而，有明显迹象表明，白宫的气候怀疑论者无法完全扭转该国大约二十年来排放量的下降。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;无论特朗普做什么，“都不会改变这一基本趋势”，以环境为重点的研究非营利组织“未来资源”的总裁兼首席执行官&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/u/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioKLUMGdg6D03F_fsLEgOOVEf32lO-bxe4jxtTzaoSFGOaXJ21l2hcPEgNpJH1oWWVm-BaJuaJ5aVpSvORC_79C4E09N2hBFc4dShYlev7wo00RQblQo1BgFhkVsCrZOz6fmCNxb9mhQXWfCrb2tM6fqA4uX4swnvFG5L69gHqRgZK9-lFWMs4o_BxBETmPvct9dK4A5KDwixsrOIHNYhSGazPkeQvQKJPOFKzGhGj3_mAlofYGOLQvYbcvs29apkzFwTTTdWOdDUN3SZwcOLzA-3twsLboDLUdNfBhI4B2I9oXpSrreAx6Z_KQ3uKUTr8snh5QZYQO_6OESG-MkqKgz49kDL18MR3oZujNGUVoVu"&gt;比利·皮泽尔&lt;/a&gt;表示。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;尽管如此，特朗普并不需要扭转甚至暂停美国排放量的下降来将气候变暖推向灾难性的水平。当整个世界（不仅仅是美国） &lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp13LCssMz9wcfYTbfuyCUBrt5WhbRM5oRMdHuWvvzy7jmfIRE2E-wDpQluPmSDElOhJDKM62QvdmxLR0_DM56RrjvqKsuYhyKHjFzdHgVfLFOi85uxZxWFvm7XL8EZKce7n546AcxsRy7kbifDpLoSrBtH-Y__AHypIfAtDN3a9lMweuhgitNYCKRoOl_HQrqXvvZt6BcNqzzhdeULRI7OpSolMruhBWQYSOLZSZ7SZhzotC8poU2oEraqNQ1Q4jYNsUdx83VbRWhhlFkfEdpUabUVdRqOFpSzxzQjT-5qvI2rUD5YeRxszeZtavVYrjHxeFHhpAFneYGeFp23xPKgvVkwhbLnoEQkRC7QEEVDn9QoOuodvbsUfw3unZ64Lb7q46pl4m7qDFoqrs7QTkc8EMkk3CQnDB2oX0dTFZ70H8EXrRuWE7Jks5rTNMdSWJ0gnpxuTaZ5lmgzfste2l2NGU5pmI45AHfE0qM7EpBA2B2_vcRmK8YYYg-8a0UFmjW9AhpsT3FOxKC8sXIbPhHaQWKruTc3GC4YSC6PkGVgzygrpU9Ej5GjODHvwAshcW4leo7aKmvXXdTBFQNIKvis0kV69LnwGWw6FExpFTY79zBobACjVgaFUJX8OLR7JPYmM4p6L_C3T-wGL7wKVd04Dmn0Cfs6rdgVrezwP1ZDTG5FOSgqz__ktiTgH9QDDnbnpxL3ZvzZQGuscB5olH4OtZ5Bm5f6XnROrhG5tzPd1UTzHrxM95kBk8bJGeiTOLZDsB4-uWu_dc-HKnTtrObKmw%3D%3D"&gt;在应对气候变化方面已经落后&lt;/a&gt;时，任何进一步的放缓都将导致全球变暖进一步加剧，这意味着更多毁灭性的灾难。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;为了更好地了解特朗普再次上任后美国的排放状况，以及未来四年、十年或二十年的情况，首先回顾一下过去是有帮助的。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="body-image" style="margin: 20px 0px;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp1st13HQkN_dIeFtwjGsmOgDxgf_VDCKn4wLjLfdNMdLe9Xn1iMRikcYiriEltD4TIef9kPQfQ0V-jRSUA8ZZx3_ErY6vGLm5ZZGZeFJlQqrODCKTirY5YIbtB_LGgFPAz9lGZCgvxKjA-iWPf05lvaOzdx9PZ-4RSMwIq8y04nvyUBtUERXvek24iIVSkvs4tFpEZ-mtP7kVbA9C-0iIMcw-vT6A7-FM69ho0wWCqMJELW6AmJ8tfvXGi_UdfGKvFjQxJ5ehVRtfG9bsuJUSzyKBMz_6V_c-LHfZ_uMGfDTF-OZLkD47xIYxX8_vtbjJTrcJ3qWoyCglY5je5g7VAwbz6s_jwT7IOu-Hx_iCckaqcqh7ST9vsrZk8vk8IBufbQ_Qy_OfAnmgJBqskqBEBhtw8jJg8vqFnRQ8HgkryynsCJ6ZvTkm7_I2Z8FdcScopAEMy2ufwYmJBcEuzO1JeoKqILxUYqL7FRipWVmbbhn7T6TMSg8Z3TSEqIw_4a1XA5uFrF1-5vfKoXSthKzT9G4Z--f8TjDMdTnJmRP1frFYukqXJAml-9EuEM5Xw0m5bAkPLHkpUDWxiZ61VLGoJzTO9FGU63k3WQF0aFIe4rNibY1paAOzdindO0okf0_c7NPJM33tQCBKPW1HdRJGsjureAeAZsU4IJBquQLtOAut7vfXlApTwRbiDNuq_TIX11T-0WmG0-S34Qco7O9qUVbo5_IH9UaDP2yQBH3QehdNgaEEhelzkcwdvbZXZXPP3" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;table width="550"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/ikb.v8N83I3E/v3/pidjEfPlU1QWZop3vfGKsrX.ke8XuWirGYh1PKgEw44kE/-1x-1.png" width="550"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt; &lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/ikb.v8N83I3E/v3/pidjEfPlU1QWZop3vfGKsrX.ke8XuWirGYh1PKgEw44kE/-1x-1.png" style="display: block; width: 530px; margin: auto;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;美国总排放量于 2007 年达到峰值，此后一直在大幅下降。但麻省理工学院斯隆管理学院应用经济学教授&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/u/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLYqsiQd4Xu54K_vz71hNJNVaVnTxbAYfX_cEBVnWkVmJi7uiDiIorIjWpURx0Ub2Amlc0e9CIcy4Q1oY_97YtFfOKWA8A82RkeuNHZwv-GDRUbBeiXubSzzVHwFvnwqW-xz0osCx0aDRiTHRFDri_SFVVY9o4QGqfv8RgBjkh7dPpzoSwINpbHSuSXbzn7Qrp0ib8E5R1ZCqJ0cvGvA58A6JL1FUyb2TM_60_8Ox15RMcXnn4PiRcmsFDChyoxsnDk_Lqvtn3kQ94E7z0unWy-PMJpCrFijhUZdhlkb2x1M1dZCQBIdVsn9Y-wItteAT-Q2tFfjSGvpXHyZAkonmyA4tjB4AnZvyWrYQicgDcTs7du_lmOZZX7dkhuZhjdvv84-Oxg46pn_hDo7zNbmLLP0Z9r-PDI1v6YARKFcA02R"&gt;凯瑟琳·沃尔夫拉姆（Catherine Wolfram）&lt;/a&gt;表示，特别是“真正引人注目”的两年——2009年和2020年，她曾短暂担任拜登财政部负责气候和能源经济的副助理国务卿。这两年都经历了经济衰退。沃尔夫勒姆解释说，这两次美国的排放量都大幅下降，这表明“能源和经济增长是如何紧密相连的”。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;从长期趋势来看，近期下降背后有一个主要驱动因素：电力行业不再使用煤炭。荣鼎集团能源和气候业务副总监本· &lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/u/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioPSDVlq0DV1m9v59dzImd-uurMulA_bWwAP8Ru4kDxvWJ34jJgxEAUNPwJX_zGw-ICVbYGWuKSZlLif1p2BHvDKM5yAlrcLcWYiC6FmcYkB2WSF216wAeJ-NVTmDk-B9aYoRJwfQ5v4DVc6vE3KPcrnnHCeKU_RgvLs00GarcY92pW0HEkYSKy0E6rhU-oyZk0JFZYHo7zQPHrXAACVPtX8R0li6uqPE3vvZORn76Vh3gnXlLubnWGHuV6Udh753-c02AUWACYBbTaa9ZqWrN83F2Gd9ztoWEClmqgtbVwXrJMr5sir23K6h9EZMlQpLFljq1L5TCe10bX3_cvDvimI%3D"&gt;金 (Ben King)&lt;/a&gt;表示，2000 年代中期开始的水力压裂革命导致了廉价天然气的兴起，导致天然气越来越多地取代碳密集型煤炭作为电力来源。与此同时，“风能、太阳能和电池等可再生资源的可用性也不断增加”，金说。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="body-image" style="margin: 20px 0px;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp1st13HQkN_dIeFtwjGsmOgDxgf_VDCKn4wLjLfdNMdLe9Xn1iMRikcYiriEltD4TIef9kPQfQ0V-jRSUA8ZZx3_ErY6vGLm5ZZGZeFJlQqrODCKTirY5YIbtB_LGgFPAz9lGZCgvxKjA-iWPf05lvaOzdx9PZ-4RSMwIq8y04nvyUBtUERXvek24iIVSkvs4tFpEZ-mtP7kVbA9C-0iIMcw-vT6A7-FM69ho0wWCqMJF6E0-Cij6HK7i0Fq09bF0GyGVQVuFd55Zj6pq00Z0uS8fpKlLOgl4NG-VYjUHe47WqyRR3WOnlAG0w9ns3Rj0vpEoExhaUR42IbIzPkURYNuQd99TNGe2n5j7ElvZU28NPMH7Un4Xbikv_OiZu2NrP6gU75vk_rCMnPn1uTRpwZ3cSBZ251w0rv4Z9lULwOUR5mimq99ClDLKyNqJ36dmRQM0bgmhUZra40mnZyLsAC4HDCig-6UEbp5Goh0MlM1p6oubCjgO0WAt3mIkReLegk8s7ydy8PcIbg04gZvKazGBr9dnE7-jyt_GK_7qpL5B6nhKlB6ZWmGQZ-08vcvq2nLvAZFv4tqf1uXJSEhcKun51mFM1Vn2hR9sknlOUm6AqizrWDLU8wT9FzwIiShJ4A9uIOzFSKFhNVx8LnXnDU5axcjmgDz30DbH71_nhOWn2Y7l6fFc1raOt3g7RTeOwUp8FyKtSY-Y9bZzWnNRUWtnqd6bhvMjyWFhjaQS3rc0sjU9CIeO1fwAd0QJcNmaQ" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;table width="550"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/i0LPGTmP7uVc/v3/pidjEfPlU1QWZop3vfGKsrX.ke8XuWirGYh1PKgEw44kE/-1x-1.png" width="550"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt; &lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/i0LPGTmP7uVc/v3/pidjEfPlU1QWZop3vfGKsrX.ke8XuWirGYh1PKgEw44kE/-1x-1.png" style="display: block; width: 530px; margin: auto;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;除了煤炭的进一步减少之外，电力行业的急剧下滑将越来越多地来自于可再生能源在竞争中击败天然气，但在天然气如此便宜的情况下，如果没有政策措施，清洁能源将很难超越天然气。这就是为什么拜登政府采取了多项措施鼓励可再生能源的建设，包括&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/u/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioEYhacHaTgFqfmVQ-zxMcdPRYtC0zjtn_zeO3FTdeWxcg_8rpR64weTqlRG2MKpwmNpXrOKzfhJvi55HIwNRJAPq1tJVgrketdikyinQxooEQZqJrY_qvL6Zl7ZUYniGcsKcejKb43V1D3onHN1QmuUsYWVu4pn9NrKE3lmFWojXAjUghyzUaHTMdypmLPNPRJ-NCoOsUwmVnvl3ofyp3b3ESoAN5n2z_kGoL8Ti8Xe3uvtjaqJlv8TVZV_HNQvufqxAcTmMkWWUNJvgMF7OS4qT0x97gpQwvTnzH0C7vTE4M8KGMBLUODtTytn-EOLFbkpJBwTV3OifTq0v7w8JjkbntdjG_tmzE0LRgNlttqP3FPxS1sWOhPxnBKHItB2U9aFTmU4o29YA2TgDIitmjvT548AiiAfZ-zNHE6qv9ifs-M714qGypA2ddbAhDyl0Se3o14tYLqq1TosWhUU12JOsZjzNgZuSPomN5qBD5q41ibCaqqYMPsrfk2cBNm205IrS3mHYxEG5XRDmTexXwl4GIqa6kTXScepvVpqcBPo0"&gt;批准了 11 个海上风电项目&lt;/a&gt;，这些项目的总发电量将超过 19 吉瓦。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;这是特朗普可能产生令人不寒而栗的影响的一个领域。他不喜欢风能， &lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/u/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioBnhi8M_BpbL6BJuB8irwrHUk67k2gNQc-uQolaY_zKYlo8hpOxyTAeU8DXHa2KcfXtiON35Med0Dv5igyoLZ7XfIvY9k3Dqe63kB6fpXex6G6rXBg3S7VLluG9eY8f2d-Lwh7fr7SCmHz_dBvC4UX8OynIr0xIw_6MDcNKUG2HuM3Hj4FcZ74FhMHoVSS6DCMJGsyYltqb_rqcG4Td8qBzZNFMIOyGCMy_mJZYs3VA2EqKdCycw2F3hpOcxZ93g97CKALdBQhckvgITYUbPBgAd-OB8cNQ5Sm-txK5OohWaEwQDASpqw9fWriMtOjeMNuRWCjOjeDI4fdCBnjjnnMtrhjIzjRV0AGPjILBEd9iBfuRuiJjeHhs1bIAuKkfjgEcuv4NVW6VrnN-e-i5noXJL-RT_5REMOL8ld8wY7jA_oDAWqYJmniPjgw8Sf8fhrHA1HiusSXP6bxID4HHeZrDHIR0Y8JoTJWp_IElkHsqodmqZC5L2zPb7CBznD3Mj0U-TgXJUYao_Dh7-SUOPZMo%3D"&gt;据报道他正在考虑暂时停止新的海上风能项目&lt;/a&gt;。 BloombergNEF 的分析师并不认为这是一个无用的威胁，他们将 2024 年至 2035 年美国海上风电预测下调了 29%。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;特朗普领导下的电力部门排放可能发生的另一个复杂因素是电力需求的不断增长，部分原因是&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp1aaEd3g91vhGnv2aODPaOIfVlMFYtSlIxBJWDjnONwM0Ea7X97jY05PBnrXaIcyNBHyW7-mCu4_sqRdy0qUIvxXaOOfsAW3MPIXtJOJkcwoAbGJpI6IxNqLNuOd4P9_izI5_OKKP3hOYS1Xxg8jRi--4EnE0jqP-kr0P655yc66PgKqk3QQCco2qu4lC7hhMUpLaNTajCr7dq22B2HUkZWgtME4_a09Q9YTLdYkTrfTBltGiA6BXk2LzVY6Wt9gPAx4r37IxnQS33ZbtLBMZ1HC8KAqrrkz_e-NoZWvkqLORiZ8jvG-ipGm33grwjVCiRNhKE1vnHENpEy2wG59ZqBHpIB65cjbMTEwBYNtJ942Zw8kH5hI-eyiYrNVbbEqeYz0QDR58vESLRNCgI_T4HY4N0O9FdemPnx4zKSqlWzKzLh6Jx0BnSwpwIJ314M4LRWqO8Ka9s94Ed6p5Y-QlUhkbPDsrnQJBsKEHfoAJK5Hnck7dI6LwjqfIjtkHdXTi86k02k56M4t6mmLDxiZ0wgmAWDOCboMwy5ux2cCcf-pKj6sgv7CQwUQO6alFrv9qlHUxEtH-6GyrcJ6U7nSjUr7_UKcTBrhJvfGl_BX6B0UG2IjnrXubJS8NuhBw-AfTnobebBQ5oKueha-DTc0VbQ1K7E4NBh6dKzCRtdVb0hUcXezkDocXHIboybrAZ_OoQJv9eaMhTB_UGb0Rm1Zjsdfu8anJKQBqAypnZ2_yfqeTXeKpzT1RXQMy1rMBLr9mhLcEDZ3C-Y9vG5966i3eDx0kjA1rHDl4NBzhdr6F5XcY%3D" target="_blank"&gt;夏季炎热&lt;/a&gt;以及人工智能和数据中心的快速增长。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;金说，除了电力行业外，所有其他主要行业——交通、建筑、工业——的排放基本上“一直在闲置，到处都没有什么变化”。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;拜登政府采取的一些重大气候举措旨在开始改变这一现状，特别是在交通运输领域，例如新的车辆污染标准和《通货膨胀减少法案》中&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp17hf1PP8wMN-4syrL3AMBFnGyTdHPqBrX-1S4Q0Pj--pNfFhSumUqgQJ3RtV57_o4Aw_3tvbwFaIhob4LYX6CgfckLVv6HFcyS-t0jblfeDbjOV8iH2xUcwnpt174VnafcFfa9HH4YFbYnPjSqZH2fXgxVR5GGJKqGQmNgYtYrsX1pgl59ImQHkLiMqS-bo8jjpmzSTBkikreSksAbKHSILxa4ZF5bsG9lFTYI8FBNvm5wTRPWhGvpjehBpfqffTyQWaVNI_yZl7CbDc_WbbaIY18MGgk-lRp8trsQzDsyiF3VdfN5k1qX3cIGQFI3suen-hVuf2BsqqS1uo47gDIwZ1vJKxt49jd0nWu6D_rf5tMQsBRKaw4quSM0z3EwbBORnVfxEgIBH82-K1Fmap51p_rcpXa5ok37U0rjnuEV17hXmfMXOvH7-IzjkJHeYBxSFP1g7uPXWWHibRUnv3i1HVxnoh5KoJjxzgbo7bSo1kCuT95FaLsqDDjiEcK2frn1XMn3DX9MXdteEJI3VW030yFh2a-EbQ-StD3WOjYE92_luIaBqZCM9RrV415Wg1moaw0oxVEqnTcVZH1jDUj0m2WenB-PrsCAynJAOnRCN-J73R2XyaVAMLQXx_xW8mGRjgxMVaLbi5XuqZLOIjavGGIFv7xLPpMU7-FdFYcQvkNTi9K43BlgCO0DY6F5bSISxzRkkLJ1H5FdOKi0AlMBDqAOFCY7Wkv0B6BL3mXaxQDCEeMeJOWeFrBq7JwU2yt0Co9pr8fg4W1OLA7rf4DZA%3D%3D" target="_blank"&gt;对电动汽车的消费者激励措施&lt;/a&gt;。这些努力很重要，因为随着美国电力部门排放量的下降，交通运输部门成为美国最大的排放源。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;但这些政策的影响才刚刚开始显现，而特朗普正准备揭开这些政策的面纱。彭博新能源财经将 2030 年电动汽车占新乘用车销量的预测从特朗普赢得大选前的近 50% 下调至 33%。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;因此，专家们对未来四年的情况感到悲观。皮泽尔表示，虽然目前尚不清楚拜登的气候遗产将在多大程度上被抵消，但毫无疑问，气候政策不会进步或变得更强。 “时间正在流失，”他说。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;请在 Bloomberg.com 上阅读&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/click?_t=f574328d4d0c4c359b90d8e49b10e21d&amp;amp;_m=82ee7bd0468f47509e3dd7c3f6323fe1&amp;amp;_e=krdzJ4SE8a0X3Y7UBiYioLh5w6eufltGxXvZa1ZKqhuI9ac3G9syn7JF6M4VcUp1st13HQkN_dIeFtwjGsmOgDxgf_VDCKn4wLjLfdNMdLe9Xn1iMRikcYiriEltD4TIef9kPQfQ0V-jRSUA8ZZx3_ErY6vGLm5ZZGZeFJlQqrODCKTirY5YIbtB_LGgFPAz9lGZCgvxKjA-iWPf05lvaOzdx9PZ-4RSMwIq8y04nvyUBtUERXvek24iIVSkvs4tFpEZ-mtP7kVbA9C-0iIMcw-vT6A7-FM69ho0wWCqMJEz6i9_UHbkzhxRslNQb1VfWzDQqUKz5668jzLQQifd8zY5-wN4Ny13oD-UHjUcIt5DRyVclg2KrCSSZYCKHkRs01vEcEEg299-4gNKP6vnJh9L2mct6qjNCVSphrd3l9qfdK0JCpY5sjvCKjpQRp6PcVOppfXc4MJ_kijMbEpyAK40F4q43sbt4h9N6hR70HP18iGp0pH13cbGqWMG7SM30E_i7ghDMb23gJs-uKlkZHUYZsF9Su0ozxRfv_LZHypdIQzLMRhnyihkRB1301WkAg4j9JqZUhYLtzPynH1sjW5rzC-veAuRxEu3riSb94Jqr5wqoPpmLkjWU-SnxR5nKvqiXFrhD8ZZT9